---
<DocsLayout
  title="API Reference · QuickZTNA Docs"
  description="Complete REST API reference. 57 routes, action-based dispatch, JWT auth, post-quantum-signed sessions. Curl, Node, Python, Go, CLI, Terraform examples."
  current="api"
  sidebarVariant="api"
  threeCol={true}
  prev={{ href: "/quickstart", label: "Quickstart" }}
  next={{ href: "/cli", label: "CLI reference" }}
>
  <!-- ============ LEFT: CONTENT ============ -->
  <div id="overview">
    <div class="eyebrow"><span class="eyebrow-dot"></span>API Reference · v1</div>
    <h1>QuickZTNA API</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      The QuickZTNA API is organized around REST. It uses action-based dispatch
      inside a single-handler pattern, returns JSON-encoded responses wrapped in a
      consistent envelope, and takes JWT bearer tokens or org-scoped API keys.
      57 public endpoints across 10 logical groups.
    </p>

    <div class="definition">
      <span class="endpoint-method method-post">POST</span>
      <span>https://login.quickztna.com/api/key-management</span>
    </div>

    <p>
      Creates a new <a href="#create-auth-key">auth key</a> — the credential
      used by the <code>ztna</code> agent installer to enrol a device. Reusable
      keys cover fleet rollouts (100 devices in 2 minutes via MDM or Ansible);
      ephemeral keys are ideal for CI/CD runners that disappear when idle.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- ============ AUTH ============ -->
  <div class="api-section">
    <h2 id="authentication">Authentication</h2>
    <p>
      Every authenticated request carries a bearer token in the
      <code>Authorization</code> header. QuickZTNA supports three credential types:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>JWT access token</strong> — ES256-signed, 1-hour TTL. Issued by <code>/api/auth/login</code> and rotated via <code>/api/auth/refresh</code>. Used by the dashboard SPA.</li>
      <li><strong>API key</strong> — long-lived, revocable, org-scoped. Used by SCIM, Terraform, and your own automation. Created via <code>action: "create_api_key"</code>.</li>
      <li><strong>Node key</strong> — machine-to-server credential issued at first registration. Used only by the <code>ztna</code> agent for heartbeat and key exchange.</li>
    </ul>

    <Callout type="warn" title="Keep your keys safe">
      API keys carry tenant-wide privileges. Never expose them in client-side
      code, mobile apps, or public repos. Use <code>rotate_api_key</code> on a
      90-day rotation schedule.
    </Callout>
  </div>

  <!-- ============ ENVELOPE ============ -->
  <div class="api-section">
    <h2 id="envelope">Response envelope</h2>
    <p>
      Every response is wrapped in a consistent envelope. Application-level
      success is in <code>success</code>, payload in <code>data</code>, and
      failures populate <code>error</code> with a machine-readable code and a
      human-readable message.
    </p>
    <CodeBlock samples={[{
      lang: "Success",
      code: `{
  <span class="tok-p">"success"</span>: <span class="tok-k">true</span>,
  <span class="tok-p">"data"</span>: { <span class="tok-c">/* payload */</span> },
  <span class="tok-p">"error"</span>: <span class="tok-k">null</span>
}`
    }, {
      lang: "Error",
      code: `{
  <span class="tok-p">"success"</span>: <span class="tok-k">false</span>,
  <span class="tok-p">"data"</span>: <span class="tok-k">null</span>,
  <span class="tok-p">"error"</span>: {
    <span class="tok-p">"code"</span>: <span class="tok-s">"ERROR_CODE"</span>,
    <span class="tok-p">"message"</span>: <span class="tok-s">"Human-readable"</span>
  }
}`
    }]} />
  </div>

  <!-- ============ CREATE AUTH KEY ============ -->
  <div class="api-section">
    <h2 id="create-auth-key">Create an auth key</h2>
    <p>
      Creates an auth key that the <code>ztna</code> agent uses to enrol devices
      into your tailnet. The key appears in the
      <code>ZTNA_AUTH_KEY</code> environment variable read by the installer.
    </p>

    <div class="definition">
      <span class="endpoint-method method-post">POST</span>
      <span>/api/key-management</span>
      <span style="color:var(--text-muted)">·</span>
      <span style="color:var(--text-muted)">action: "create_auth_key"</span>
    </div>

    <h3 id="parameters">Body parameters</h3>
    <div class="params-table">
      <ParamRow name="action" type="string" required={true} desc='Must be <code>"create_auth_key"</code>. Do not use the generic <code>"create"</code> — that form does not exist and will 404.' />
      <ParamRow name="org_id" type="string" required={true} desc="The organization ID this key belongs to. You must be an admin or owner of this org." />
      <ParamRow name="reusable" type="boolean" desc="If <code>true</code>, the key can enrol multiple machines. Required for fleet rollouts. Default <code>false</code> (one-shot key)." />
      <ParamRow name="ephemeral" type="boolean" desc="If <code>true</code>, enrolled machines auto-deregister when they go offline. Useful for CI runners and containers. Default <code>false</code>." />
      <ParamRow name="expires_in" type="integer" desc="Seconds until the key becomes invalid. Minimum <code>300</code>, maximum <code>2592000</code> (30 days). Default <code>3600</code> (1 hour)." />
      <ParamRow name="tags" type="array of strings" desc='Tags applied to machines enrolled with this key. Prefix with <code>tag:</code> — e.g. <code>["tag:laptop", "tag:prod"]</code>. Used in ACL rules.' />
      <ParamRow name="description" type="string" desc="Optional human-readable note for audit. Max 255 chars." />
    </div>

    <h3 id="returns">Returns</h3>
    <p>
      Returns an <code>auth_key</code> object on success. The <code>key</code>
      field is only returned on creation — you cannot retrieve it again later.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <h2 id="auth-endpoints" style="margin-top:64px;">Authentication endpoints</h2>

  <h3 id="auth-signup">POST /api/auth/signup</h3>
  <p>Create a new user account. Returns JWT pair + refresh cookie on success. Rate-limited to 5 per IP per 5 min.</p>
  <CodeBlock samples={[{ lang: "curl", code: `$ curl <span class="tok-u">https://login.quickztna.com/api/auth/signup</span> \\
    -H <span class="tok-s">"Content-Type: application/json"</span> \\
    -d <span class="tok-s">'{
      "email": "you@company.com",
      "password": "Str0ngP@ssw0rd!",
      "full_name": "Your Name"
    }'</span>` }]} />
  <ResponseBlock status="201 Created" body={`{
  <span class="tok-p">"success"</span>: <span class="tok-k">true</span>,
  <span class="tok-p">"data"</span>: {
    <span class="tok-p">"user_id"</span>: <span class="tok-s">"user_5k4aLw3Jm"</span>,
    <span class="tok-p">"email"</span>: <span class="tok-s">"you@company.com"</span>,
    <span class="tok-p">"email_verified"</span>: <span class="tok-k">false</span>,
    <span class="tok-p">"token"</span>: <span class="tok-s">"eyJhbGciOiJFUzI1NiIs..."</span>,
    <span class="tok-p">"refresh_token"</span>: <span class="tok-s">"rt_7K9xqP4BmT..."</span>,
    <span class="tok-p">"expires_in"</span>: <span class="tok-n">3600</span>
  },
  <span class="tok-p">"error"</span>: <span class="tok-k">null</span>
}

<span class="tok-c">// Set-Cookie: __Host-refresh_token=rt_...; HttpOnly; Secure; SameSite=Strict; Path=/; Max-Age=2592000</span>`} latency="412ms" />
  <Callout type="info" title="Anti-enumeration">
    If the email is already registered, signup returns 201 with a placeholder UUID — not a 409 conflict. This prevents attackers from enumerating registered emails.
  </Callout>

  <h3 id="auth-login">POST /api/auth/login</h3>
  <p>Exchange email + password for JWT pair. TOTP required if MFA is enabled (returns 403 <code>MFA_REQUIRED</code> if code missing). Rate-limited 10 per IP and 10 per email per 5 min.</p>
  <CodeBlock samples={[{ lang: "curl", code: `$ curl <span class="tok-u">https://login.quickztna.com/api/auth/login</span> \\
    -H <span class="tok-s">"Content-Type: application/json"</span> \\
    -d <span class="tok-s">'{
      "email": "you@company.com",
      "password": "Str0ngP@ssw0rd!",
      "totp_code": "487392"
    }'</span>` }]} />
  <ResponseBlock status="200 OK" body={`{
  <span class="tok-p">"success"</span>: <span class="tok-k">true</span>,
  <span class="tok-p">"data"</span>: {
    <span class="tok-p">"user_id"</span>: <span class="tok-s">"user_5k4aLw3Jm"</span>,
    <span class="tok-p">"email"</span>: <span class="tok-s">"you@company.com"</span>,
    <span class="tok-p">"token"</span>: <span class="tok-s">"eyJhbGciOiJFUzI1NiIs..."</span>,
    <span class="tok-p">"refresh_token"</span>: <span class="tok-s">"rt_7K9xqP4BmT..."</span>,
    <span class="tok-p">"expires_in"</span>: <span class="tok-n">3600</span>
  },
  <span class="tok-p">"error"</span>: <span class="tok-k">null</span>
}`} latency="186ms" />

  <h3 id="auth-refresh">POST /api/auth/refresh</h3>
  <p>Rotate the access token. Browsers send <code>__Host-refresh_token</code> cookie automatically; CLI sends <code>refresh_token</code> in body. Server deletes old refresh token and issues a new pair (single-use rotation).</p>
  <CodeBlock samples={[{ lang: "curl (cookie)", code: `$ curl <span class="tok-u">https://login.quickztna.com/api/auth/refresh</span> \\
    -X POST \\
    -b <span class="tok-s">"__Host-refresh_token=rt_..."</span> \\
    -d <span class="tok-s">'{}'</span>

<span class="tok-c"># CLI / non-browser: POST /api/auth/refresh with {"refresh_token":"rt_..."}</span>` }]} />
  <ResponseBlock status="200 OK" body={`{
  <span class="tok-p">"success"</span>: <span class="tok-k">true</span>,
  <span class="tok-p">"data"</span>: {
    <span class="tok-p">"token"</span>: <span class="tok-s">"eyJhbGciOiJFUzI1NiIs..."</span>,
    <span class="tok-p">"refresh_token"</span>: <span class="tok-s">"rt_8Ly4rN2xQ..."</span>,
    <span class="tok-p">"expires_in"</span>: <span class="tok-n">3600</span>
  },
  <span class="tok-p">"error"</span>: <span class="tok-k">null</span>
}`} latency="42ms" />

  <h3 id="auth-me">GET /api/auth/me</h3>
  <p>Return the authenticated user's profile. Checks JWT, checks blacklist (returns 401 if password was changed).</p>
  <CodeBlock samples={[{ lang: "curl", code: `$ curl <span class="tok-u">https://login.quickztna.com/api/auth/me</span> \\
    -H <span class="tok-s">"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN"</span>` }]} />
  <ResponseBlock status="200 OK" body={`{
  <span class="tok-p">"success"</span>: <span class="tok-k">true</span>,
  <span class="tok-p">"data"</span>: {
    <span class="tok-p">"id"</span>: <span class="tok-s">"user_5k4aLw3Jm"</span>,
    <span class="tok-p">"email"</span>: <span class="tok-s">"you@company.com"</span>,
    <span class="tok-p">"full_name"</span>: <span class="tok-s">"Your Name"</span>,
    <span class="tok-p">"avatar_url"</span>: <span class="tok-k">null</span>
  },
  <span class="tok-p">"error"</span>: <span class="tok-k">null</span>
}`} latency="18ms" />

  <h3 id="auth-mfa-setup">POST /api/auth/mfa/setup</h3>
  <p>Generate a new TOTP secret. Scan the returned URI with an authenticator, then call <code>/api/auth/mfa/verify</code> with the first 6-digit code to activate + receive 10 backup codes.</p>
  <CodeBlock samples={[{ lang: "curl", code: `$ curl <span class="tok-u">https://login.quickztna.com/api/auth/mfa/setup</span> \\
    -X POST \\
    -H <span class="tok-s">"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN"</span>` }]} />
  <ResponseBlock status="200 OK" body={`{
  <span class="tok-p">"success"</span>: <span class="tok-k">true</span>,
  <span class="tok-p">"data"</span>: {
    <span class="tok-p">"secret"</span>: <span class="tok-s">"JBSWY3DPEHPK3PXP"</span>,
    <span class="tok-p">"uri"</span>: <span class="tok-s">"otpauth://totp/QuickZTNA:you@company.com?secret=JBSWY3DPEHPK3PXP&issuer=QuickZTNA"</span>
  },
  <span class="tok-p">"error"</span>: <span class="tok-k">null</span>
}`} latency="24ms" />

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <h2 id="keys-endpoints" style="margin-top:64px;">API keys</h2>

  <h3 id="create-api-key">POST /api/key-management (action: "create_api_key")</h3>
  <p>Create a long-lived, revocable API key for machine-to-machine use (SCIM, Terraform, CI/CD). Admin-only.</p>
  <CodeBlock samples={[{ lang: "curl", code: `$ curl <span class="tok-u">https://login.quickztna.com/api/key-management</span> \\
    -H <span class="tok-s">"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN"</span> \\
    -H <span class="tok-s">"Content-Type: application/json"</span> \\
    -d <span class="tok-s">'{
      "action": "create_api_key",
      "org_id": "org_9fX2kRmBnqT4",
      "name": "terraform-ci",
      "scopes": ["machines:write", "acl:write", "dns:write"]
    }'</span>` }]} />
  <ResponseBlock status="200 OK" body={`{
  <span class="tok-p">"success"</span>: <span class="tok-k">true</span>,
  <span class="tok-p">"data"</span>: {
    <span class="tok-p">"id"</span>: <span class="tok-s">"ak_Pq7r2wXK"</span>,
    <span class="tok-p">"key"</span>: <span class="tok-s">"qz-api-live-4N8mR3w..."</span>,
    <span class="tok-p">"name"</span>: <span class="tok-s">"terraform-ci"</span>,
    <span class="tok-p">"scopes"</span>: [<span class="tok-s">"machines:write"</span>, <span class="tok-s">"acl:write"</span>, <span class="tok-s">"dns:write"</span>],
    <span class="tok-p">"created_at"</span>: <span class="tok-s">"2026-04-19T18:00:00Z"</span>,
    <span class="tok-p">"revoked"</span>: <span class="tok-k">false</span>
  },
  <span class="tok-p">"error"</span>: <span class="tok-k">null</span>
}`} latency="38ms" />

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <h2 id="machines-endpoints" style="margin-top:64px;">Machines</h2>

  <h3 id="register-machine">POST /api/register-machine</h3>
  <p>Agent-side registration. Called by the <code>ztna</code> installer with an auth key. Server generates <code>node_key</code>, allocates tailnet IP, returns machine ID.</p>
  <Callout type="warn" title="Field name gotcha">
    Use <code>name</code> (not <code>hostname</code>). The backend silently ignores <code>hostname</code>.
  </Callout>
  <CodeBlock samples={[{ lang: "curl", code: `$ curl <span class="tok-u">https://login.quickztna.com/api/register-machine</span> \\
    -H <span class="tok-s">"Authorization: Bearer tskey-auth-abc123"</span> \\
    -H <span class="tok-s">"Content-Type: application/json"</span> \\
    -d <span class="tok-s">'{
      "name": "laptop-alex",
      "os": "linux",
      "wireguard_pubkey": "abcdef0123...",
      "pqc_pubkey": "ML-KEM-768 bytes..."
    }'</span>` }]} />
  <ResponseBlock status="200 OK" body={`{
  <span class="tok-p">"success"</span>: <span class="tok-k">true</span>,
  <span class="tok-p">"data"</span>: {
